cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with semantic segmentation of medical images using deep learning techniques, specifically fully convolutional networks (FCN). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses principal component analysis (PCA) to aid in feature detection, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning also suggests a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with multi-channel fMRI data, which is a type of medical imaging (cs.MM).
